{{Infobox Shinto shrine
| religious_affiliation = 
| image                 = Nashinoki.jpg
}}
{{Interlanguage link|Nashinoki Shrine|ja|梨木神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Kamigyō-ku]]. It was never a Beppyo shrine but is considered by many to be equivalent to one.

It is one of the newest Shinto shrines in Kyoto being built in 1885<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fushimi Inari Taisha {{!}} Location {{!}} Shajiraku – Quality traditional food and cultural experiences at Kyoto shrines and temples. |url=https://www.shajiraku.jp/en/plan/location_detail.php?id=2 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=社寺楽 Shajiraku |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-10-04 |title=Nashinoki Shrine Kyoto, a Bush Clover Shrine {{!}} All About Kyoto |url=https://allaboutkyoto.com/en/nashinoki-shrine-kyoto/ |access-date=2023-04-07 |language=en-US}}</ref>

It hosts a [[Bush clover]] festival<ref>{{Cite web |title=Hagi Matsuri |url=https://www.discoverkyoto.com/event-calendar/september/hagi-matsuri-nashinoki-shrine/ |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=Discover Kyoto |language=en}}</ref>

